tor><![CDATA[JasonM1]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Give this man a raise.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/QdB2Biz</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ep6ZMPi.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/QdB2Biz</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Headcase444]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Land of the &quot;Free&quot;</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/7EAMiOJ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4agBavA.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/7EAMiOJ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[JasonM1]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>What WOULD Jesus do?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/SSnpoLt</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4WzGydd.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/SSnpoLt</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[JasonM1]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Meanwhile in France</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Zfszm0k</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/KPLYgaP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>France Just Built a Rocket Engine That Works Without Fire — And It’s a Game-Changer for Space

In a high-tech aerospace lab near Toulouse, French scientists have done the unthinkable — they’ve created a rocket engine that doesn’t burn fuel. Instead, it uses rotating plasma, confined by magnetic fields, to push spacecraft with no combustion, no moving parts, and no exhaust flames.

This is more than a clever tweak — it’s a brand-new class of propulsion. The system uses a spinning ring of ionized gas, driven by electromagnetic forces. Think of it as a controlled lightning storm, accelerating particles silently across space. It's precise, durable, and virtually maintenance-free.

In tests, the engine delivered continuous thrust for over 1,000 hours, showing zero degradation. Unlike chemical rockets that explode fuel in seconds, this engine provides steady, efficient propulsion — ideal for satellites that need long-term orbit correction, deep-space probes, or slow interplanetary journeys.

It can start or stop instantly, steer with electric precision, and function in the vacuum of space without overheating. While it currently runs on xenon, the French team is also testing argon and krypton — cheaper, lighter alternatives that open doors for mass production.

Because it doesn’t rely on combustion, it sidesteps many of the costs, risks, and environmental impacts of traditional spaceflight. And that’s why France’s space agency and its EU partners are already integrating it into upcoming micro-launchers and orbital service modules.

This may be the engine that finally turns the dream of long-range, low-cost space travel into a cold, quiet, electromagnetic reality.

#science #france</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Zfszm0k</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[TheTaoofRob]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Grandma is the best!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/C9lC4uj</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6G6dviH.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/C9lC4uj</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[AdventurousDonut480]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Of course it happened</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/wGmsjX5</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TJBJSxb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/wGmsjX5</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[psuedon]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>75 years and still functional</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Z90DWBm</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1PmD116.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Z90DWBm</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[HotCoffee9520]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Covfefe</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/obu90IP</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8vRFT6j.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/obu90IP</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ChocolatePoopy]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>???</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/zKJIQIh</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1lMjshX.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/zKJIQIh</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[AnonymousMockingjay]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The Illusion of Numbers</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/xtX6mx3</link><description><![CDATA[<